description: This course surveys standard topics in the study of algorithms, with an emphasis on complexity analysis and implementation experience. Topics include asymptotic analysis, searching and sorting, divide and conquer, basic graph algorithms, greedy algorithms, dynamic programming, and NP-complete problems. Offered annually in spring semester. Counts toward computer science major and concentration in neuroscience.
name: Analysis of Algorithms
notes: Prerequisite: CSCI 251 and a mathematics proof course.
prerequisites: CSCI 251 and a mathematics proof course.
